-- Ford says to spend $3.0 billion on Mexican plants
-- 
-- Fri May 30, 2008 12:30pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/30/us-ford-fiesta-mexico-idUSN3030776220080530

 

 MEXICO CITY  (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) Chief Executive Alan Mulally said on Friday the company and its suppliers would invest $3 billion in plants in Mexico. 

 The company had been expected to announce that it would build its new global car, the Fiesta, in Mexico for future sale in the U.S. market, according to media reports. (Reporting by  Cyntia Barrera )